  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (8e64cff 2023-10-01T00:20:28.991654440Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nanvil --prune-history 100 --transaction-block-keeper 10 --steps-tracing --silent --port 52385\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAnvil crashes with the following error message when requesting `debug_traceTransaction` for a failed tx:\r\n\r\n```\r\nthread 'tokio-runtime-worker' panicked at 'index out of bounds: the len is 0 but the index is 0', crates/evm/src/trace/mod.rs:141:45\r\nnote: run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=1` environment variable to display a backtrace\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have created a reproducible example here: https://github.com/michprev/anvil-low-gas-debugTT-crash\r\n\r\nThe issue probably is related to the fact that a contract is being created in a call that does not have enough gas (see https://github.com/michprev/anvil-low-gas-debugTT-crash/blob/main/contracts/Foo.sol).",
